* * Url Input. * * It supports the protocols: `http`, `https` * * ```javascript * const input = Input.create('myInput: url'); * input.setValue('http://www.google.com'); * ``` * *

Property Summary

* * Property Name | Description | Defined by Default | Default Value * --- | --- | :---: | :---: * maxContentSize | maximum file size of url's content in bytes | ::on:: | `5242880` (5mb) * exists | checks if the url is valid | ::off:: | ::none:: * allowedExtensions | specific list of extensions for the input (this check is case insensitive) example: ['jpg', 'png'] | ::off:: | ::none:: * * All properties including the inherited ones can be listed via * {@link registeredPropertyNames}
